The '''Metta Drop''' was a sudden drop in the [[Boonta Eve Classic/Legends|Boonta Eve Classic]] terrain used by [[Podracer/Legends|Podracers]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]].

During a [[Podracing/Legends|Podrace]] in [[32 BBY/Legends|32 BBY]], the [[Dug/Legends|Dug]] contender of the Mos Espa Raceway [[Sebulba/Legends|Sebulba]] attempted to take fellow racers [[Rimkar]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] out of the race by slamming them into the cliff face with [[Plug-F Mammoth Split-X engine/Legends|his racer's]] engines during their drop. Caught by surprise, Rimkar automatically jammed his thrusters forward, resulting in a collision with the mountain. Anakin, on the other hand, managed to avoid the crash by instinctively pulling out of the descent and narrowly colliding with Sebulba.

Not long after this incident, in the [[Boonta Eve Classic/Legends|Boonta Eve Classic]], [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker]] managed to get by the sneaky [[Gasgano/Legends|Gasgano]] and move up to the fourth place, behind [[Teemto Pagalies/Legends|Teemto Pagalies]], at the Metta Drop.

